The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 1: With the government undecided on a successor to SAIL chairman V.S. Jain, who retired yesterday, S.K. Rungta, the second in command in the company, has taken up temporary charge. Rungta and P.K. Bishnoi, director of Rashtriya Ispat Nigam, are the two contenders for the post. Their names have been forwarded to the Prime Ministers office for selection.

 Mumbai, Aug 1: Close on the heels of Asian Development Bank asking Bangladesh to consider the Tatas $3-billion investment, the group today said its proposal still stands with the government of Bangladesh. The project is still under consideration, Tata group chairman Ratan Tata said. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 1: The RBI today released guidelines governing accounting and related aspects with reference to when issued transactions in central government securities. The apex bank said all when issued securities should be recorded in the books as an off balance sheet item till the issue of the security.

 Nagpur, Aug. 1: A local court today issued a bailable warrant against Rahul Bajaj, chairman-cum-managing director of Bajaj Auto, for allegedly cheating in Karodpati Hungama Scheme for their two-wheeler sales promotion.

 Calcutta, Aug. 1: A.C. Mahajan today assumed charge as chairman and managing director of Allahabad Bank, succeeding O.N. Singh, who retired from service yesterday. Mahajan was executive director of Bank of Baroda before taking up this new assignment. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 1: Eicher Motors will seek shareholders approval for the sale of its Royal Enfield business unit to a new subsidiary company, proposed to be set up in the National Capital Region.

 New Delhi, Aug. 1: The tenure of the Rs 3,000-crore government bonds has been reduced to 10 years from the earlier scheduled maturity of 20 years and above to ensure that auction of the paper on August 8 is well received.




